Nice food but the service was not too satisfactory. Not enough waiting staff. Missed out one of our orders.

April is a bittersweet time in Hong Kong. Spring arrives for a week and the balmy weather make this bar a great place to chill out and people watch in the early evening. But by May, the temperature and humidity makes it better to sit indoors. One thing I don't like is their happy hour policy. You have to sit at the bar to get the discount. Terrace people...pay full price. Also, for a high ticket menu, the level of English was a bit wanting.
Great food, service and location.  Highly recommended if you are in the area.

reviews.text: I really love going to this station for Airport Express. It is not cheap but with HKD 20 more you can have priority check in up to 24 hours, which saves you tons amount of time from Getting in queue, get the boarding pass and check your luggage. You definitely could enjoy more time inside the airport and wait for your flight. Most airlines are included. You can always getting discount ticket from traveling companies.

Thank you for the update. Attached with the city of Kln. Are this serious? Don’t know. This is Kowloon Station and the rating is extremely high. K Y Lo desert house knows. Review more? Tell us in frequency. Be sure to subscribe to our channel and ring the notification bell to find the latest videos of sakitech. And peace out with Kowloon Station’s hotels including West.

The airport express entry gates and platforms are different and not close to the ones for the Tung Chung line. The whole station seems much bigger than it needs to be so there is a bit of walking to the gates and then to the platforms, or even to leave the station to take the airport express shuttle bus or take a taxi. The lifts are also not at the most convenient locations so again there may be a bit more walking. But generally the station is modern and clean, just not as busy as most other stations in Hong Kong most of the time especially for the airport express side.
Very nice. Short walk to train - great.

Very easy the get around when you get off the airport express. After you exit, there are taxis to the left or you can take the airport shuttle bus which is free to one of the many hotels (up the escalators) and which leave every 15-20 min. There are different routes so make sure to check before getting on a bus. Not all hotels are represented, but you can ask which hotel is closest and then walk from that stop.
